  "prompt": "Do consulting firms show their consultants' transcripts to their clients?",
  "response": "Consulting firms typically do not share their consultants' transcripts with clients. While the qualifications and expertise of consultants are important, firms generally communicate these qualifications through resumes, profiles, or summaries of their experience rather than sharing official academic transcripts. Confidentiality and privacy standards, along with professional norms, usually guide how firms manage their consultants' information. However, firms may highlight the educational backgrounds and relevant experiences of their team members during the client engagement process.",
